    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-12-28T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-12-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="424"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d424">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 342.112Sm6.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Vice Consul <persName type="from">Curtis</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Bridgeburg</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-12-28">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 28, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Walter Smith, Buffalo, N. Y., shot and killed; Charles Dorsch, Buffalo, N. Y.,
                    shot through lung by private in Canadian militia in Fort Erie this morning.
                    These men were duck shooting and did not land when ordered.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">J. B. Curtis</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
